Cowboys’ Quarterback Romo Has Punctured Lung, Broken Rib, ESPN Reports

-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 
2011-09-19T22:26:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/cowboys-quarterback-romo-has-punctured-lung-broken-rib-espn-reports.html
Dallas Cowboys quarterback  Tony
Romo  broke a rib and punctured one of his lungs during Sunday’s
27-24 victory over the San Francisco 49ers, ESPN reported,
citing people it didn’t identify.  A CT scan today revealed that Romo suffered the injury
during the game, which he finished after missing much of the
third quarter, ESPN reported. He said today that he would play
against the Washington Redskins a week from tonight.  Romo completed 12 of 15 passes in the fourth quarter and
overtime to help the Cowboys win.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  